description: Mask phone numbers in UI display; leave phone form inputs unmasked
alwaysApply: true
---

# Phone number display (UI)

Everywhere in the UI, phone numbers must be shown **masked**, except in form
fields where the user is actively entering or editing a phone number.

## Rules

- **Display** (sidebar, summaries, tables, notices that echo a stored number,
  notification channel identifiers, linked shooters, change-phone “current
  number” readout, etc.): use `maskPhoneE164` from
  `src/client/lib/maskIdentity.ts`. Do not invent a second mask format.
- **Inputs** (`type="tel"`, login/register/forgot/change-phone entry fields):
  show the value as typed — do **not** mask while editing.
- Prefer passing the raw E.164 into the mask helper at the render site; do not
  store a second “display format” unless the API already returns a masked field
  intended for UI.

## Format

`maskPhoneE164("+380501112233")` → `+380*****2233` (up to five middle digits
replaced with `*`; short numbers keep ends when possible).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw E.164 in read-only UI
<div className="role">{account.phoneE164}</div>

// ✅ GOOD
import { maskPhoneE164 } from "../lib/maskIdentity";
<div className="role">{maskPhoneE164(account.phoneE164)}</div>

// ✅ GOOD — active phone input stays unmasked
<input type="tel" value={phone} onChange={...} />
```

Worker/log masking (`maskPhone` on the server) is separate; do not reuse that
for client UI.
